    "hazardAnalysis": "Potential risks identified by a Work Area Hazard Analysis reveal primarily ergonomic strains, slips/trips/falls, and electrical hazards to prevent injuries. Key actions include assessing workstation ergonomics, maintaining clear walkways, securing cables, inspecting equipment for damage, and ensuring proper storage to prevent falling objects.",
    "riskManagementNotes": "Risk Management Fundamentals training can be conducted at https://usaf.percipio.com/",
    "trafficSafetyNotes": "The highway system in San Antonio is laid out in a wagon wheel configuration and has many bridges/fly-overs/overpasses. In inclement weather, these, along with many others, become very slick. When raining, the oil and petroleum rise to the surface causing the roads to become very slick. Flooding occurs quickly in the local area check rain before entering a low water crossing and never go around road barricades.  Freezing temperatures combined with moisture will cause the bridges/fly- overs/overpasses to freeze very quickly. Avoid those areas if possible during freezing weather. Construction is on-going throughout the city. Be aware that traffic flow and lanes can change from one day to the next. Reduce your speed in these areas.  \n",
